content.detailedDescription: I was driving home from work and talking with a friend on my cell phone. just before i reached exit 76 going south on i-85 in salisbury, i seen this white orb shoot across the highway right in front of me almost like a comet would do. the difference is that for some reason i sensed an organic presence. the orb seemed to be controlled as the car i was riving was. my feeling upon seeing this is that there is increasing activity since i had seen almost the same identical thing a week ago. once again i was on my way home from work. as i pulled into my driveway it shot horizontally directly over my back yard. this new orb flew straight across with a dissipating white trail. it seemed to disappear into the clouds.
content.summary: Orb flew straight accross the highway like a comet with a dissapating trail.

content.detailedDescription:
On november, 10, 2015, around 4:30 pm hawaiian time, i was heading back from dinner in kona, hi to my time-share in waikoloa village, hi with my two friends in a convertable mercedes with the top down.  i had just arrived a week prior and was in full-throttle, tourist mode, taking pictures and videos of almost everything i encountered.  driving at 55 mph, i alternated between still shots and video clips.  i did not intend to take any video footage but i have an iphone 6s and i believe it must take video footage without you asking it to because i have five video clips and five pictures that show a blue disk in the sky, and a blue laser-like orb dancing around our car and around my head.  i only saw the objects yesterday because i uploaded all my photos and videos to my computer to see my tourist footage and show friends.

my friend i was showing the footage to noticed the blue orb in the sky from a still shot and asked me if i knew what it was.  i did not, so we zoomed in on it and it appeared to be shaped like a human stomach but it glowed blue on the exterior and white in the center.  we kept looking at the pics and eventually we came to a video of the same footage.  it was very electrifying because in the video footage, we saw a blue orb moving sparadically in our vehicle, mostly around my straw-hatted, head while the glowing, stomach-shaped object in the sky gradually changed into a circle.

i do not recall my feelings being anything other than elated the entire month i stayed on the island and the work i was doing there came out exceptionally well.

i am sharing the original video footage and pictures of this encounter and i welcome someone, or something to please explain what i saw.
content.summary: I was taking pics of the landscape and noticed two blue orbs in my pictures after downloading them to my computer.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking my dog across from calvary cemetery along lake michigan at 9:35 p.M. saw a bright light in the sky offshore. i remember thinking "how pretty, looks like the star of bethlehem." upon closer examination, it was actually four lights in a diamond pattern, each glowing at the same intensity. lots of airplanes in sky at the same time, maybe four or five as the cemetery is on the approach to runway 22n at o'hare (hubby is a pilot). this did not look like a plane, it looked kind of like the pleides, only much brighter and a bit bigger (and besides the pleides has seven stars with only six usually visible). this was really very bright. it was completely stationary. another dimmer diamond moved north to south toward the first diamond. it wasn't as bright. but when it "passed" the first diamond (about 2-3 degrees underneath, difficult to estimate speed), it changed color to bright red and kept going. it wasn't a plane, nor was it a helicopter. we have those frequently (we are on the flight path between two major trauma centers). these things made no sound, and the bright white one hovered for at least 10 - 15 minutes. another person came walking along and i pointed it out to her. just then a cloud covered it, but you could still see the lights for another minute or two and then the cloud completely covered it. helicopters sometimes show four lights (usually only three) and their lights are more "linear;" they also have a green and/or red light to indicate port and starboard. this thing looked like a diamond on a playing card, very precisely spaced lights at each corner. and it never moved or changed shape, just disappeared when the clouds covered it. i felt awe when i saw it and was happy when another person came along and saw it also. hope this helps. call me if you want more info.
content.summary: Craft 1: bright white diamond shaped light, stationary. craft 2: also diamond-shaped, changed from white to red after passing first craft

content.detailedDescription: Leaving for work at 6 am, on pulling out of my drive and looking west, in the sky i observed a large object with a row of flashing lights. now this object was in the sky where small planes would fly, not very high, but it filled up 1/3 of my windshield.It was massive, i watched it as it headed in a straight line west, but all of a sudden it disappeared. it didn't accelerate or zoom off it just disappeared. its december no tree leaves to get in the way or block the view. i'm not sure what i saw, but my father was a avid plane watcher, we spent a lot of time doing this. i live 35 miles ne of kansas city mo this was not in the normal flght approach for kci, most off those are coming and going behind my home.  we see military flights out of whiteman afb all the time, this didn't fit anything from there either. i was raised to be open minded, but this left me feeling rather apprehensive and afraid. i can't help but wonder if anyone else saw this.

content.detailedDescription: I had just gotten home from work, and was upstairs in my bedroom, and looked out my window that faces west. the sky looked really beautiful. the sky looked pink and red in the horizon, after the sun had set. it was about 5:45 p.M. it was dusk and getting darker. i saw a very bright star to the west, so i was looking at it for awhile. all of a sudden it slowly moved to the south, then flashed , and disappeared! the bright light was gone. i couldn't see any sign of it anymore, like it just disappeared. i kept looking out my window to see if it would reappear, but it didn't. i didn't see any planes or jets flying nearby either. it didn't look like a plane or jet. i was surprised when i saw it move, since i thought it was a bright star! then when it flashed and disappeared i was excited and wondered if it was a ufo! something made me stand there and stare at it for awhile, while it was moving, which was kind of strange!
content.summary: Looked to the west and saw bright star that moved slowly, then flashed and disappeared

content.detailedDescription: I stepped out onto my north porch to look for my dog and something above me to the east caught my attention as i looked at it       i saw it moving at a very high rate of speed, silent and in two seconds it passed at about 55 degrees  to the north above me and abruptly did a right turn. it made a slight and very tight curve to the north and shot away in another second. nearly a sharp 90 degree turn. i have never seen any plane or chopper ever do that. i am a former navy aircraft mechanic, 1977 honorable discharge usn, last duty station was nas, north island, san diego, calif. my father is a  air force master sergeant/tail gunner on b-52. i know aircraft and what they can do and this seemed impossible. the g-force of that turn would have been brutal. not a sound at all. it took approx. 6 seconds to go from east of yuma about 4 miles when i first saw it, to about ten o'clock to my left and shoot north and was gone. not any sound at all. three lights fairly close together. it may have been very large but it was difficult to tell. if it was small it was very close to me. if it was very large it could have been several miles away. i ran inside and told my mother i care for about it and posted it on my facebook and then ran back out to see if there was any other sign of it. after looking and watching and waiting for about five minutes i went back in and added some more to my facebook post and then it suddenly dawned on me that i should report this to mufon.  i once saw a craft above the rocky mountains as a teenage in high school with several friends in 1974. it was gigantic and was casting a shadow over several peaks in the mountains to the west of denver and almost as quick as i saw it and pointed it out to my friends and they saw it, it went from gigantic to a pin point in less than two seconds and was gone west from denver. then one other time in 1983, at night walking my wife home from her bus stop i saw something making a swishing sound going over head but could not see what was making the air noise until i looked really hard and could see an oblong/oval shape of stars moving across the sky above us. i pointed out to my wife sheryl and she bill holnesssaid she saw something moving but wanted to know what it was. it was silent as well and seemed to be very large and appeared to recreate the stars that were behind it on it's surface. the only way i even realized it was there was because the pattern of  stars were shifting slightly as it went over our heads. it moved slowly compared to this sighting and the one in 1974. i seemed  to feel ok at first after it flew away but within a half hour i felt sick, like severe indigestion and heartburn  -bill holness
content.summary: Spotted an object traveling at a high rate of speed. i t did a near absolute right angle turn and flew north from yuma, co.

content.detailedDescription: While traveling east on arizona highway 389 about 20 miles west of fredinia arizona my wife and i traveling in separate vehicles observed three airplanes that were a very dark grey in color without any markings. they were large four engine planes with approximately 100' wingspans.  what was most unusual was that they were flying at about 40mph and were less than 100' off of the ground.  i was certain the first one i saw was going to crash because it seemed impossible for such a large craft to stay airborn at such a slow speed.  the second plane came towards me at about the same speed but was tilting the wings about 80 degrees as it flew over a power line nearly hitting the line with its wing.  these craft seemed to be without weight.  the strangest part was they made no sound of any kind. two of them flew directly over my vehicle at less than 40' of altitude.  i opened my window a little and there was no wind or exhaust from the large jet engines and absolutely no sound.  i was in a moving van with my wife following in her car and she observed the very same things. there were another 3 or 4 cars that must have seen them too.  they seemed to be almost playing as they swung back and fourth tilting there wings at angles that should have stalled any aircraft i know of. i have not been able to identify the planes.  the outer 10-15 feet of the wings sloped down about 5 degrees.  i called 911 and was told that us military planes often practiced in that area.  these planes must have had anti-gravity and a different type of propulsion than forced air through jet turbines.  i have asked around my town in southern utah and others claim to have seen the same planes.  they were in sight for quite a while.  i was traveling 60mph eastbound and they were flying westbound at extremely slow speeds.  the one that banked 80 degrees over the power lines must have slowed to 20mph or less.  it almost seemed to hover at that steep angle.  the things they did were not possible by conventional craft.  again there was no sound or wind of any kind. i'm certain they were ours but not anything i can find on any sight.  i could clearly see the cockpit windows but because of glare could not see inside. these were very large planes.
content.summary: Appeared to be unmarked military aircraft.
